{"id":"1805.00966","submitter":"Jonas Wittbrodt","authors":"Isabell Engeln, Margarete M\\\"uhlleitner, Jonas Wittbrodt","title":"N2HDECAY: Higgs Boson Decays in the Different Phases of the N2HDM","comments":"24 pages, no figures. N2HDECAY is available at\n  https://gitlab.com/jonaswittbrodt/N2HDECAY as source code","journal-ref":"Comput.Phys.Commun. 234 (2019), 256-262","doi":"10.1016/j.cpc.2018.07.020","report-no":"DESY 18-064, KA-TP-09-2018","categories":"hep-ph","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  The program N2HDECAY calculates the branching ratios and decay widths of the\nHiggs bosons of the Next-to-Two-Higgs-Doublet Model (N2HDM). The code\nincorporates the dominant higher-order effects by including QCD corrections and\noff-shell decay modes. The N2HDM is an extension of the Standard Model by a\nHiggs doublet and a real Higgs singlet. Its phenomenology can change\ndramatically depending on which global symmetries are broken by electroweak\nsymmetry breaking. It can feature a large visible Higgs sector in the broken\nphase, behave like a 2HDM with scalar singlet dark matter in the dark singlet\nphase, or, in the inert doublet phase, extend an inert doublet model by mixing\na singlet with the SM Higgs boson. N2HDECAY provides precise predictions for\nthe decays of the Higgs bosons in all of these phases.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 2 May 2018 18:27:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-10-19"}
