le, the\nscattering kernel for all models is markedly non-Gaussian at 1.3 mm but is\nstraightforward to calculate and depends only weakly on the assumed model for\nthe wandering of the magnetic field direction. On the other hand, in all\nmodels, the refractive substructure depends strongly on the wandering model and\nmay be an important consideration in imaging Sgr A* with the EHT.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 3 May 2018 11:56:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-05-04"}
