{"id":"1805.01368","submitter":"Mentor Stafa","authors":"Daniel A. Ramras and Mentor Stafa","title":"Homological stability for spaces of commuting elements in Lie groups","comments":"56 pages, accepted version","journal-ref":"Int. Math. Res. Not. IMRN 2021, no. 5, 3927-4002","doi":"10.1093/imrn/rnaa094","report-no":null,"categories":"math.AT","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  In this paper we study homological stability for spaces ${\\rm\nHom}(\\mathbb{Z}^n,G)$ of pairwise commuting $n$-tuples in a Lie group $G$. We\nprove that for each $n\\geqslant 1$, these spaces satisfy rational homological\nstability as $G$ ranges through any of the classical sequences of compact,\nconnected Lie groups, or their complexifications. We prove similar results for\nrational equivariant homology, for character varieties, and for the\ninfinite-dimensional analogues of these spaces, ${\\rm Comm}(G)$ and ${\\rm\nB_{com}} G$, introduced by Cohen-Stafa and Adem-Cohen-Torres-Giese\nrespectively. In addition, we show that the rational homology of the space of\nunordered commuting $n$-tuples in a fixed group $G$ stabilizes as $n$\nincreases. Our proofs use the theory of representation stability - in\nparticular, the theory of ${\\rm FI}_W$-modules developed by\nChurch-Ellenberg-Farb and Wilson. In all of the these results, we obtain\nspecific bounds on the stable range, and we show that the homology isomorphisms\nare induced by maps of spaces.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 3 May 2018 15:21:34 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 29 Jun 2018 15:42:59 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 26 Jun 2019 16:21:35 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Tue, 28 Apr 2020 19:19:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-03-16"}
